item.title: CVE-2023-47678|2024-06-04T17:26:37.714Z -- asustek%20computer%20inc. -- rt-ac87u
item.description: An improper access control vulnerability exists in RT-AC87U all versions. An attacker may read or write files that are not intended to be accessed by connecting to a target device via tftp.

item.title: CVE-2023-31195|2023-06-13T00:00:00 -- asustek%20computer%20inc. -- asus%20router%20rt-ax3000
item.description: ASUS Router RT-AX3000 Firmware versions prior to 3.0.0.4.388.23403 uses sensitive cookies without 'Secure' attribute. When an attacker is in a position to be able to mount a man-in-the-middle attack, and a user is tricked to log into the affected device through an unencrypted ('http') connection, the user's session may be hijacked.
